                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>The text of the Vita has some characteristics of the so-called "Ḥayq recension" of Gadla Takla Hāymānot. Cp. Mss. EMML n<locus target="1834">1834</locus> (EMML V, 310-14); BN, Éth. 342 (GrébGriaule II, 18-20), Ṭānāsee 162 (SixTana III, 202-06). For a (rough) French translation of the text s. J. DUCHESNE-FOURNET, Mission en Éthiopie, 1<ref type="mss" corresp="ES901190">901-190</ref>3, vol. 1, Paris 1908,<ref type="mss" corresp="ES340431">340-431</ref>.</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>The text of the Miracles basically coincides with that of Ms. Éth. 343 (GrébGriaule II, 21-25); miracle 17 is absent from Éth. 343; miracle 18 is identical to miracle 17 of Éth. 343.</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>Decorated quire marks.</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
